quran[56]{c,v,t}:
  74,1,O you wrapped up
  74,2,Arise and deliver your warning
  74,3,And praise your Lord
  74,4,"And your garments, keep free from stain"
  74,5,And avoid all abomination
  74,6,"Nor expect from giving, any increase"
  74,7,"But for your Lord’s sake, be patient and constant"
  74,8,"Finally, when the trumpet is sounded"
  74,9,"That day, will be a day of distress"
  74,10,Far from easy for those without faith
  74,11,Leave Me alone with those that I created alone
  74,12,To whom I granted resources in abundance
  74,13,And children to be by his side
  74,14,To whom I made life smooth and comfortable
  74,15,Yet he is greedy. Should I add even more
  74,16,"By no mean, because to Our signs he has been rebellious"
  74,17,Soon I will visit him with a mount of disasters
  74,18,For he thought and he plotted
  74,19,"Oh, how he plotted"
  74,20,"Yes, woe to him, how he plotted"
  74,21,Then he looked around
  74,22,Then he frowned and he scowled
  74,23,Then he turned back and was arrogant
  74,24,"Then said he, “This is nothing but deception, derived from those before"
  74,25,“This is nothing but the word of a mortal.”
  74,26,Soon I will cast him into hellfire
  74,27,And what will explain to you what hellfire is
  74,28,"Nothing does it permit to endure, and nothing does it leave alone"
  74,29,Darkening and changing the color of human beings
  74,30,Over it are nineteen
  74,31,"And We have set none other than angels as guardians of the fire. And We have fixed their number only as a challenge for unbelievers, in order that the people of the Book may arrive at certainty, and the believers may increase in faith, and that no doubts may be left for the people of the Book and the believers, and that those in whose hearts is a disease, and the unbelievers may say, “What meaning does God intend by this?” So God leaves to stray whom He pleases, and guides whom He pleases, and none can know the forces of your Lord except Him. And this is no other than a warning to humanity"
  74,32,"No, indeed by the Moon"
  74,33,And by the night as it retreats
  74,34,And by the dawn as it shines forth
  74,35,Indeed it is one of the greatest
  74,36,A warning to humanity
  74,37,"To any of you who chooses to press forward, or to fall behind"
  74,38,Every soul will be held responsible for its deeds
  74,39,Except the companions of the right hand
  74,40,They will be in gardens. They will ask
  74,41,Those who were corrupt
  74,42,“What led you into hellfire?”
  74,43,"They will say, “We were not of those who prayed"
  74,44,“Nor were we of those who fed the indigent
  74,45,“But we used to speak vainly with vain people
  74,46,“And we used to deny the Day of Accountability
  74,47,“Until there came to us that which is certain.”
  74,48,Then will no intercession of intercessors profit them
  74,49,Then what is the matter with them that they turn away from advice
  74,50,As if they were affrighted animals
  74,51,Fleeing from a lion
  74,52,Still each one of them wants to be given scrolls spread out
  74,53,"By no means, but they are not conscious of the hereafter"
  74,54,"No, indeed it is a reminder"
  74,55,Let any who wills keep it in remembrance
  74,56,"But none will keep it in remembrance except as God wills. He is the Lord of righteousness, and the Lord of forgiveness"